    {
      "id": "pred-bulk-empty-after",
      "kind": "round-trip",
      "description": "delete-emails-imap emptied the sgt-bulk staging folder. GUARDS THE FIX shipped in this track: the runner used to call client.search() WITHOUT {uid:true} — imapflow answers with SEQUENCE numbers — and then passed that list to messageFlagsAdd/messageDelete with {uid:true}, reinterpreting sequence numbers as UIDs. The two agree only in a virgin mailbox; anywhere else it deleted the WRONG messages (or none) while still reporting success with a deletedCount.",
